olour relations increases with increasing\nsSFR, for example, the slope for post-starburst galaxies can be flattened to\n$0.45$ from the global value $0.87$ in the $M_*/L$ vs. $g-r$ diagram. Hence\nconverting galaxy colours to $M_*/L$ should be done carefully, especially for\nthose galaxies with young luminosity-weighted stellar ages, which can have\nquite different star formation histories.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Aug 2021 01:21:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-25"}
